OL,6,FLawyers representing the Government
OL,7,Fsought to overturn the judge's
OL,8,Ffindings and award of damages.
OL,10,FPaul McLaughlin KC, for the Secretary
OL,11,Fof State, stressed to the Court of
OL,12,FAppeal judges of Lord Justice Horner,
OL,13,FMr Justice McFarland and Mr Justice
OL,14,FRooney that a public inquiry has not
OL,15,Fbeen ruled out.
OL,17,FHe argued it was wrong to conclude the
OL,18,FGovernment believed the PSNI and PONI
OL,19,Freviews might fulfil the Article 2
OL,20,Fobligations.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/19
