OL,6,F"What the Secretary of State made
OL,7,Fabsolutely clear is that he was simply
OL,8,Fdeferring a decision to be taken at a
OL,9,Flater point in time, so he could be
OL,10,Finformed of that process, and that a
OL,11,Fpublic inquiry would be (an option) on
OL,12,Fthe table," the barrister said.
OL,14,F"We say that the judge went too far."
OL,16,FDisputing the findings which led to
OL,17,Fthe #5,000 award made to Mrs Finucane,
OL,18,Fcounsel claimed a failure to properly
OL,19,Fdistinguish any culpable delay.
