OL,6,F"He took no steps whatsoever to ensure
OL,7,Feither the PSNI or PONI were able to
OL,8,Fdeliver their respective process with
OL,9,Fdue expedition.
OL,11,F"The Secretary of State should have
OL,12,Fanticipated, at the very least, that
OL,13,Fthere was a real risk of delay given
OL,14,Fwhat had happened in the past.
OL,16,F"Despite this, no steps were taken to
OL,17,Fprevent such delay blighting these
OL,18,Fproceedings.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/19
